ugh the Event Bus (Property 2).\n```\n\n**File:** `D:\\code\\temp\\SpecForge\\packages\\observability\\src\\event-bus\\index.ts`, lines 4-5\n```\nImplements Property 2: Event Bus Traversal\nAll cross-layer communication must pass through Event Bus\n```\n\nThis is enforced in the code at:\n- `EventBus.ts` line 159: `async publish()` — \"All cross-layer communication must go through this method (Property 2)\"\n- `observability/event-bus/index.ts` lines 21-23: `async emit()` — \"Implements Property 2: All cross-layer communication must pass through Event Bus\"\n\n#### 1.4 Property 7: \"WAL-first Guarantee\"\n\n**File:** `D:\\code\\temp\\SpecForge\\packages\\daemon-core\\src\\daemon\\Daemon.ts`, lines 77-78\n```\n// Bridge: persist every state transition to WAL via StateManager\n// This is the WAL-first guarantee (Property 7)\n```\n\n**File:** `D:\\code\\temp\\SpecForge\\packages\\daemon-core\\src\\wal\\WAL.ts`, line 67\n```\nWAL ordering: events.jsonl is fsynced BEFORE any state.json update.\n```\n\n---\n\n### 2. IS EVENTBUS THE SOLE EVENT PERSISTENCE MECHANISM?\n\n**No.** There is a **dual-write problem** documented extensively in INV-001:\n\n**File:** `D:\\code\\temp\\SpecForge\\.specforge\\specs\\INV-001\\findings_report.md`\n\n- **Line 18 (C1 - Critical):** `events.jsonl` has **two independent write paths** — WAL and EventBus→EventLogger write the same file through different file handles.\n- **Line 23 (M2 - High):** EventBus → EventLogger produces **duplicate event writes** — each state transition event is written twice.\n- **Lines 37-45:** The two paths:\n  - **Path A:** `StateManager.transition()` → `WAL.appendEvent()` → `fs.appendFile(eventsPath)` → `fs.open('a')` → `handle.sync()` → `handle.close()` (WAL.ts lines 68-85)\n  - **Path B:** `EventBus.publish()` → `persistenceHook` (EventBus.ts line 168) → `eventLogger.append(event)` (Daemon.ts line 166) → `fs.open(eventsPath, 'a')` → `fileHandle.write(line)` → `fileHandle.sync()` → `fileHandle.close()` (EventLogger/index.ts lines 327-343)\n\n- **Lines 49-65:** The WAL rotation creates a critical race window — `rotateIfNeeded()` calls `fs.rename(eventsPath, archivePath)` then `fs.writeFile(eventsPath, '')`. Between steps 1 and 2, EventLogger writing to the old handle loses data in the renamed file.\n\n- **Lines 386-401 (M2):** The duplication mechanism:\n  1. `StateManager.transition()` → `WAL.appendEvent()` → writes to events.jsonl (1st write)\n  2. StateManager (or caller) publishes event via `EventBus.publish()` → `persistenceHook` → `EventLogger.append()` → writes to events.jsonl (2nd write)\n\n---\n\n### 3. WHY WAS EVENTBUS INTRODUCED ALONGSIDE THE EXISTING WAL?\n\nThe spec reveals they serve different **architectural purposes** — but ended up overlapping in persistence:\n\n| Component | Purpose | Spec Origin |\n|-----------|---------|-------------|\n| **WAL** | Durable write-ahead logging with fsync. Guarantees crash recovery. Is the \"source of truth\" for state. | TASK-2 (E1 Daemon Core) — State Manager + WAL |\n| **EventBus** | Cross-layer **pub/sub communication**. Decouples subsystems. Enables mode filtering, SSE push, event-driven reactions. | TASK-11 (E2 Observability) — Unified Event Schema + Event Bus |\n\n**File:** `D:\\code\\temp\\SpecForge\\.specforge\\specs\\WI-001\\tasks.md`\n- TASK-2 (lines 76-122): WAL is defined as part of State Manager infrastructure (Epic 1, Daemon Core). It is for **persistence**.\n- TASK-11 (lines 497-541): EventBus is defined as part of Observability (Epic 2). It is for **communication and routing**, with mode switch filtering, CAS offloading, and SSE push.\n\n**File:** `D:\\code\\temp\\SpecForge\\.specforge\\specs\\INV-001\\findings_report.md`, lines 406-423 (FIX-C1 recommendation):\nThe investigation confirmed these were designed independently and recommends:\n> \"Unify events.jsonl write path to a single Writer. Make WAL the **sole writer** of events.jsonl. EventLogger should not write directly to the file — it should call WAL.\"\n\nThe root cause is that both components were given the same file path (`~/.specforge/runtime/events.jsonl`) during construction:\n- **Daemon.ts line 54:** `new StateManager(pathResolver, pathResolver.resolveDaemonRuntimeDir(), true)` — creates WAL pointing to `events.jsonl`\n- **Daemon.ts line 95:** `new EventLogger(runtimeDir)` — same `runtimeDir`, creates its own handle to `events.jsonl`\n- **Two components, same target file, zero coordination.**\n\n---\n\n### 4. INTENDED RELATIONSHIP BETWEEN EVENTBUS, WAL, EVENTLOGGER, AND STATEMANAGER\n\n#### 4.1 The Design Intent (from WI-001 specs)\n\n```\nEventBus ←── (pub) StateManager, HTTPServer, ExtensionLoader, PermissionEngine, WorkflowEngine\n    │\n    ├── persistenceHook ──→ EventLogger ──→ events.jsonl (events log)\n    │\n    ├── ModeSwitch.filter() ──→ SSE push to subscribers\n    │\n    └── subscribed handlers (SessionRegistry, KnowledgeTrigger, AgentRoster)\n\nStateManager.transition() ──→ WAL.appendEvent() ──→ events.jsonl (state transitions, fsync'd)\n```\n\nThe **intent** was:\n1. **WAL** is for state transitions — the authoritative, fsync-guaranteed persistence of state machine transitions. (Property 7)\n2. **EventBus** is for cross-layer communication — any subsystem can publish events, and any subsystem can subscribe. (Property 2)\n3. **EventLogger** is the EventBus's persistence adapter — receives events via `persistenceHook` and writes them to `events.jsonl`.\n4. **StateManager** is the in-memory state + WAL coordinator — it writes state transitions to WAL first, then updates memory.\n\n#### 4.2 The Actual Implementation (revealed by INV-001)\n\n**File:** `D:\\code\\temp\\SpecForge\\.specforge\\specs\\INV-001\\findings_report.md`\n\nThe reality is more problematic:\n\n**Dual-write (C1):** The WAL and EventLogger both write to the **same** `events.jsonl` file. The WAL was meant for state transitions; EventBus→EventLogger was meant for general events. But they target the same file, leading to:\n\n- **Duplicate writes (M2, lines 386-401):** When a state transition occurs, WAL writes it. Then the StateManager (or caller) publishes the event via EventBus, and the persistenceHook writes it AGAIN through EventLogger. The same logical event appears twice in `events.jsonl`, in two different serialization formats (daemon-core Event format vs observability Event format).\n\n- **Type incompatibility (C4, lines 99-138):** daemon-core's `Event` interface (types.ts line 42-75) has `actor?: string`, `projectId?: string`, `category?: string` (all optional). observability's `Event` (types/index.ts) has `actor: AgentIdentity | null` (required), `projectId: string` (required), `category: EventCategory` (required). The bridge at **Daemon.ts line 166** uses `event as unknown as import('@specforge/observability').Event` — an unsafe runtime cast that can cause validation exceptions.\n\n- **EventLogger not initialized (C5, lines 141-167):** `Daemon.start()` calls `stateManager.initialize()` (line 151) but **never** calls `eventLogger.initialize()` (line 94-115 of EventLogger). This means `lastEventId` stays `null`, `eventCount` stays `0`, and `getStats()`, `getLastEventId()`, `getEventCount()` all return incorrect data.\n\n- **Triple overwrite of state.json (C2, lines 70-97):** Three components independently write `state.json`: StateManager (line 418), EventLogger (line 491), RecoverySubsystem (line 495). All use `fs.writeFile()` with Last-Write-Wins semantics, no locking or version checking.\n\n#### 4.3 How EventBus is Wired (Daemon.ts)\n\n**File:** `D:\\code\\temp\\SpecForge\\packages\\daemon-core\\src\\daemon\\Daemon.ts`\n\nConstruction (lines 48-125):\n| Line | What Happens |\n|------|-------------|\n| 50 | `this.eventBus = new EventBus()` — created first |\n| 54 | `this.stateManager = new StateManager(...)` — creates internal WAL pointing to `events.jsonl` |\n| 66 | `new SessionRegistry(this.eventBus, ...)` — SessionRegistry subscribes to EventBus `session.*` events |\n| 72 | `new ProjectManager(this.eventBus, ...)` — injected for event publishing |\n| 74 | `new ExtensionLoader({}, this.eventBus)` — injects EventBus for extension events |\n| 95 | `this.eventLogger = new EventLogger(runtimeDir)` — points to same `events.jsonl` as WAL |\n| 97-118 | `new HTTPServer({..., eventBus: this.eventBus, ...})` — HTTPServer receives EventBus for SSE and publishing |\n\nStartup (lines 127-198):\n| Line | What Happens |\n|------|-------------|\n| 151 | `stateManager.initialize()` — WAL seeded from existing `events.jsonl` |\n| 153 | `recoverySubsystem.checkAndRepair()` — consistency check + repair |\n| 159 | `eventBus.start()` — EventBus now accepting publications |\n| **163-167** | **`eventBus.setPersistenceHook(...)`** — **The critical bridge:** every EventBus publish now calls EventLogger.append(), writing to `events.jsonl` (duplicating what WAL already writes for state transitions) |\n| 170-171 | `sessionRegistry.start()` + `projectManager.start()` — these subscribe to EventBus |\n\nShutdown (lines 330-356):\n| Line | What Happens |\n|------|-------------|\n| 282-291 | Graceful shutdown registers `eventbus-drain` task |\n| 346 | `eventBus.stop()` — clears subscriptions and buffer |\n\n#### 4.4 Known Producers and Consumers of EventBus\n\n**Producers** (who calls `eventBus.publish()`):\n| File | Line | What |\n|------|------|------|\n| `Daemon.ts` | 359 | `broadcastEvent(event)` |\n| `HTTPServer.ts` | 174, 384, 828 | SSE broadcast, HTTP event ingestion |\n| `ExtensionLoader.ts` | 201 | Extension lifecycle events |\n\n**Consumers** (who subscribes):\n| File | Line | What |\n|------|------|------|\n| `SessionRegistry.ts` | 107-117, 908 | Subscribes to `session.*` events for session lifecycle management |\n| `HTTPServer.ts` | 539-589 | Subscribes for SSE push to connected clients |\n\n**Persistence Hook:**\n| File | Line | What |\n|------|------|------|\n| `Daemon.ts` | 163-167 | `eventBus.setPersistenceHook(...)` — routes all events (with projectId) to `EventLogger.append()` |\n\n#### 4.5 The Knowledge Graph\n\n**File:** `D:\\code\\temp\\SpecForge\\.specforge\\knowledge\\graph.json`\n\nThe knowledge graph was searched for EventBus references — **no entries found**. The KG does not currently contain any nodes or relationships about EventBus.\n\n#### 4.6 Summary of the Relationship\n\n```\n                         ┌──────────────────────────────┐\n                         │          EventBus             │\n                         │  (Property 2: Cross-layer     │\n                         │   pub/sub communication)       │\n                         │                              │\n                         │  - publish(event)             │\n                         │  - subscribe(topic, handler)  │\n                         │  - buffer (1000 events)       │\n                         │  - category-based routing     │\n                         │  - observability hooks        │\n                         └──────┬───────────┬───────────┘\n                                │           │\n                     persistenceHook    fan-out to\n                          │           subscribers\n                          ▼               │\n               ┌──────────────────┐   ┌──┴──────────────┐\n               │   EventLogger    │   │ SessionRegistry  │\n               │  (observability  │   │  (session.*)     │\n               │   package)       │   │ HTTPServer (SSE) │\n               │                  │   │ KnowledgeTrigger │\n               │ append(event)    │   │ AgentRoster      │\n               └────┬─────────────┘   └─────────────────┘\n                    │\n         ┌──────────┴──────────────┐\n         │   events.jsonl          │  ◀══ SAME FILE! (C1 bug)\n         │   (same file as WAL!)   │\n         └─────────────────────────┘\n                    ▲\n                    │\n         ┌──────────┴──────────────┐\n         │         WAL             │\n         │  (Property 7: WAL-first │\n         │   fsync guarantee)      │\n         │                         │\n         │  appendEvent(event)     │\n         │  createEvent(...)       │\n         │  readAllEvents()        │\n         └────────────┬────────────┘\n                      │\n         ┌────────────┴────────────┐\n         │     StateManager        │\n         │  transition(...) → WAL  │\n         │  persistState() →       │\n         │    state.json           │\n         └─────────────────────────┘\n```\n\nThe intended design was: **WAL** for state transition persistence (property 7), **EventBus** for cross-layer communication (property 2), and **EventLogger** as the EventBus's write-to-file adapter. But in practice, WAL and EventLogger both write to the same `events.jsonl` through independent file handles, creating duplicate writes, type incompatibilities, and concurrency bugs.\n\nThe INV-001 investigation's recommended fix (lines 406-423): **Make WAL the sole writer** of `events.jsonl`. EventBus's `persistenceHook` should route through WAL, and EventLogger should become a read-only memory index/query layer.\n</task_result>\n</task>","metadata":{"parentSessionId":"ses_183dd3320ffeEB0AiZQ55MG54v","sessionId":"ses_1839535e8ffeSfKmz9nyfVMIDG","model":{"modelID":"deepseek-v4-pro","providerID":"deepseek"},"truncated":false},"title":"Search EventBus specs and role","time":{"start":1780203833884,"end":1780203973811}},"id":"prt_e7c6ab191001vSXHmaTd2D6rEO","sessionID":"ses_183dd3320ffeEB0AiZQ55MG54v","messageID":"msg_e7c6a9991001iVWFRDzYTTGxXb"},{"reason":"tool-calls","snapshot":"4aa0bc486c8a41a19134ee73a1bcc553736b92ff","type":"step-finish","tokens":{"total":85269,"input":110,"output":376,"reasoning":175,"cache":{"write":0,"read":84608}},"cost":0.000833924,"id":"prt_e7c6cee1f0010I3cgHEwnL7IbR","sessionID":"ses_183dd3320ffeEB0AiZQ55MG54v","messageID":"msg_e7c6a9991001iVWFRDzYTTGxXb"}]},{"info":{"parentID":"msg_e7c6a995a001G6wIpzHYB5Fkmg","role":"assistant","mode":"sf-orchestrator","agent":"sf-orchestrator","path":{"cwd":"D:\\code\\temp\\SpecForge","root":"D:\\code\\temp\\SpecForge"},"cost":0.003175674,"tokens":{"total":90643,"input":4200,"output":1080,"reasoning":115,"cache":{"write":0,"read":85248}},"modelID":"deepseek-v4-pro","providerID":"deepseek","time":{"created":1780203974541,"completed":1780204001741},"finish":"stop","id":"msg_e7c6cef8d001nqgNaYdymyQvdU","sessionID":"ses_183dd3320ffeEB0AiZQ55MG54v"},"parts":[{"snapshot":"4aa0bc486c8a41a19134ee73a1bcc553736b92ff","type":"step-start","id":"prt_e7c6cf2c0001SrhPVktUsaqiUz","sessionID":"ses_183dd3320ffeEB0AiZQ55MG54v","messageID":"msg_e7c6cef8d001nqgNaYdymyQvdU"},{"type":"reasoning","text":"Excellent! The exploration agent has done a thorough analysis. Let me now present the findings clearly to the user, synthesizing the spec requirements vs actual implementation.\n\nThe key insight is:\n- **Spec intent**: WAL is for state transition persistence (Property 7), EventBus is for cross-layer pub/sub communication (Property 2), and EventLogger is the EventBus's write-to-file adapter\n- **Reality**: WAL and EventLogger both write to the same `events.jsonl`, creating the dual-write problem\n\nLet me present this concisely.","time":{"start":1780203976144,"end":1780203978723},"id":"prt_e7c6cf5d0001KLaLnmMtZqXH8W","sessionID":"ses_183dd3320ffeEB0AiZQ55MG54v","messageID":"msg_e7c6cef8d001nqgNaYdymyQvdU"},{"type":"text","text":"## EventBus：规格要求 vs 实际实现\n\n---\n\n### 一、规格怎么说\n\nEventBus 和 WAL 在 WI-001（V6 架构）中被定义为**两个不同层次、不同职责**的组件：\n\n| 组件 | 所属 Epic | 职责 | 关键属性 |\n|------|----------|------|---------|\n| **WAL** | Epic 1 — Daemon Core | **持久化** — 带 fsync 的预写日志，状态机的权威真实来源 | Property 7: WAL-first 保证 |\n| **EventBus** | Epic 2 — Observability | **通信** — 跨层发布/订阅，解耦子系统 | Property 2: 所有跨层通信必经 EventBus |\n\n关键规格条目（均来自 `WI-001/tasks.md` 和 `design_delta.md`）：\n\n```\nTASK-2  (E1):  WAL = 状态转换持久化，events.jsonl → state.json 顺序保证\nTASK-11 (E2):  EventBus = 统一事件 schema + Daemon 内部事件总线\nADR-06:        三级模式切换（minimal/standard/deep）在 EventBus 层实现\nADR-09:        Agent Roster 通过 EventBus 订阅 workflow.completed\nPBT-OB-01:     \"Event must not be lost: all published events must eventually be written to WAL\"\n```\n\n**设计意图很清晰**：EventBus 是路由器，WAL 是硬盘。EventBus 负责把事件分发给订阅者（SessionRegistry、SSE、KnowledgeTrigger…），而 WAL 负责把事件持久化到磁盘。\n\n---\n\n### 二、EventBus 实际起什么作用\n\nEventBus 当前的**四个角色**：\n\n```\n                    ┌─────────────── EventBus ───────────────┐\n                    │                                         │\n  ① 路由器          │  publish(event) ──→ subscribe(topic)    │\n    跨子系统解耦     │  生产者：HTTPServer, ExtensionLoader    │\n                    │  消费者：SessionRegistry, SSE push      │\n                    │                                         │\n  ② 模式过滤器      │  ModeSwitch.filter(event, mode)         │\n    三级可观测性     │  minimal/standard/deep 按模式过滤       │\n                    │                                         │\n  ③ 持久化桥接      │  persistenceHook → EventLogger.append() │\n    ← 问题所在！    │  把事件写入 events.jsonl（第2次写入）    │\n                    │                                         │\n  ④ 缓冲区          │  内存缓冲 1000 条事件                    │\n    订阅者不丢事件   │  新订阅者可回溯缓冲                      │\n                    └─────────────────────────────────────────┘\n```\n\n角色 ① 和 ② 是 EventBus **本该做的**（符合规格）。角色 ③ 是**问题的根源**。\n\n---\n\n### 三、为什么出现双写\n\n规格要求 \"所有事件最终写入 WAL\"（PBT-OB-01），但实现时走了两条路径：\n\n```\nStateManager.transition()\n  │\n  ├──①→ WAL.appendEvent() ──→ fs.appendFile(events.jsonl)   ← 路径A：WAL 直接写\n  │\n  └──②→ EventBus.publish()\n           │\n           └── persistenceHook ──→ EventLogger.append()\n                                      │\n                                      └── fs.open('a') + write(events.jsonl)  ← 路径B：EventLogger 再写\n```\n\n**同一条状态转换事件，被写入了同一个文件两次**，且两次的序列化格式不同（daemon-core Event vs observability Event）。\n\n---\n\n### 四、规格意图 vs 现实的差距\n\n| 维度 | 规格意图 | 实际实现 |\n|------|---------|---------|\n| events.jsonl 写入者 | 只有 WAL | WAL + EventLogger（双写） |\n| Event 类型 | 统一的 Event schema | daemon-core / observability 两套不兼容类型 |\n| state.json 写入者 | 只有 StateManager | StateManager + EventLogger + RecoverySubsystem（三写） |\n| EventLogger 角色 | EventBus 的只读查询层 | 同时读写，与 WAL 竞争 |\n| 初始化 | 所有组件完整初始化 | EventLogger.initialize() 从未调用 |\n\n---\n\n### 五、一句话总结\n\n> **EventBus 本应是\"消息路由器\"**，负责把事件分发给订阅者。但因为 `persistenceHook` 把它也变成了\"持久化写入者\"，且写入目标和 WAL 完全相同，导致了 **C1（双写竞态）+ C2（三重覆写）+ M2（重复事件）** 这一连串问题。\n\n修复方向在 INV-001 报告中已给出：**统一写入路径，让 WAL 成为 events.jsonl 的唯一写入者**，EventLogger 降级为只读查询/索引层。需要我启动修复工作流吗？","time":{"start":1780203978725,"end":1780204001069},"id":"prt_e7c6cffe50019hXMSwo6XcvuBd","sessionID":"ses_183dd3320ffeEB0AiZQ55MG54v","messageID":"msg_e7c6cef8d001nqgNaYdymyQvdU"},{"reason":"stop","snapshot":"4aa0bc486c8a41a19134ee73a1bcc553736b92ff","type":"step-finish","tokens":{"total":90643,"input":4200,"output":1080,"reasoning":115,"cache":{"write":0,"read":85248}},"cost":0.003175674,"id":"prt_e7c6d5880001J26HfE3bzbf5GS","sessionID":"ses_183dd3320ffeEB0AiZQ55MG54v","messageID":"msg_e7c6cef8d001nqgNaYdymyQvdU"}]},{"info":{"role":"user","time":{"created":1780204401464},"agent":"sf-orchestrator","model":{"providerID":"deepseek","modelID":"deepseek-v4-pro"},"summary":{"diffs":[]},"id":"msg_e7c73730e001UecmnQaauAvqqi","sessionID":"ses_183dd3320ffeEB0AiZQ55MG54v"},"parts":[{"type":"text","text":"先对项目提交，然后启动修复工作","id":"prt_e7c73730f001x1di0w8Wp2RfA6","sessionID":"ses_183dd3320ffeEB0AiZQ55MG54v","messageID":"msg_e7c73730e001UecmnQaauAvqqi"}]},{"info":{"parentID":"msg_e7c73730e001UecmnQaauAvqqi","role":"assistant","mode":"sf-orchestrator","agent":"sf-orchestrator","path":{"cwd":"D:\\code\\temp\\SpecForge","root":"D:\\code\\temp\\SpecForge"},"cost":0.000681732,"tokens":{"total":91046,"input":32,"output":109,"reasoning":281,"cache":{"write":0,"read":90624}},"modelID":"deepseek-v4-pro","providerID":"deepseek","time":{"created":1780204401481,"completed":1780204410281},"finish":"tool-calls","id":"msg_e7c737349001QqzQs2UoIWlUyY","sessionID":"ses_183dd3320ffeEB0AiZQ55MG54v"},"parts":[{"snapshot":"4aa0b